message: guess im still confused on why it worked with said charger b4, just fine, passed apple test. and now with the same charger wont turn on, yet still shows amber light. when i was training with louis he had given me a board to work with and fix with a lower powered charger and i got nothing, no amber light, never powered up, nothing. if someone could explain that to me a bit more than "use a 60w charger" sorry if i sound rude but im trying to learn how to diag this problem.

title: [SOLVED]MacBook Pro "Core i5" 2.5 13" Retina 2012 lag
message:
It will power with any charger as long as there is some power in the battery. From an empty or no battery 13" needs 60W and 15" need 85W to power on.
Get a REAL Apple 85W charger, nothing else needs to be on your work bench, no Chinese knock offs either.
